---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Thom Arden and the cinematic world behind the music.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>The quiet after <span>the storm.</span></h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Thom Arden is a cinematic music project shaped around emotional storytelling, warm darkness and songs that feel like scenes from a film.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container story-panel">
      <article class="glass-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Artist statement</p>
        <h3>Stories deserve a voice.</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Thom Arden was created from a simple belief: no story should remain untold because its creator lacks the tools to express it.
          Through cinematic music and human storytelling, those emotions find their voice.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="glass-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Visual world</p>
        <h3>Ocean light, silhouettes, warm shadows.</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          A world shaped by the quiet after the storm: dark water, warm gold, distance, memory and the light that returns.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
